snippet.textDisplay:
I'm a huge Baron {a Baron turned into a King... that sounds legit even just by name} Corbin since he debuted in NXT and, honestly, I'm a greater fan of that gimmick than this one in regular suit, I preferred the Wolf character way more and when he came out in his own debut, with that music and with that presence I believe I was looking at a new Undertaker in a making and I actually still believe he can go there if they end this gimmick as soon as possible before it's too late.... because the risk here is that he remains chained to it forever.
I believe in "Less Is More" and that's the reason why what I would expect about him and from him right now is something shocking and genuinely intense that makes him look back into himself, acquiring depth and falling back into his original but now improved persona, when overspeaking wasn't needed... he had the imposing figure, the quickness {who else glides out and back into the ring like he does? Nobody, period!} and the most spectacular and megastar defying "out of nowhere" devastating signatures moves in all Pro Wrestling history, second only to Randy Orton's RKO: "The End Of Days" and "Deep Six"! I know there are other devastating moves out there, like Goldberg's Spear or Drew McIntyre's kick but those are all moves you see coming, you can see the whole preparation unfolding in front of your eyes... but Corbin and Orton signature moves when you even see coming they have just happened already, you know what I mean?
I believe he should go back there and push that character even further, into a modern wild primal persona who can make you hate him just for what he does more than for what he says, just like The Undertaker did for an entire 21 years streak!


Hail to Baron "The Wolf King" Corbin!!!

snippet.textDisplay:
Let me explain the different types of hate in the WWE.
1. Hate because you suck at your job (e.g. Corbin)
2. Hate because you are a good heel (e.g. Bray Wyatt and Samoa Joe).
For the latter, these days true heels are cheered because we appreciate their work more. It doesn't mean we want them as face.
Me personally I was upset when the Miz turned face.. because it doesn't suit him. His personality is not designed to be a face.
I will cheer heel miz, but will boo face miz because of their job.
Similarly AJ Styles, Shinsuke Nakamura, and Sami Zayn are all people who should have never been heels. It screwed up their carears.
You should never just 'turn' for the sake of turning.
Seth Rollins recent heel turn was great. It made sense.. it wasn't out of the blue like some schizophrenic heel turn (e.g. Daniel Bryan or Big Shows 20000th heel turn)

snippet.textDisplay: Lol Vince and his Minions still thinking that 1980's Mentality still gets Over in almost 2020. Cheer the Good Guy, Boo the Bad Guy. RESPECT is how Every Wrestler Gets Over. They either like your Character, Moveset and Evolution or they Don't, You Earn Respect Over Time. Fans of Wrestling pick a Certain Group of Wrestlers that they think should be put in Each Catagory that should be Pushed and Promoted. Unfortunately Vince and the WWE also choose their Favorites. And they Control Everything so it's the Fans Job to Voice Distain for the Current Direction of Whomever gets Pushed that Might Not Deserve or Fit that Mold as Well as another less Promoted Wrestler. snippet.textDisplay:
You know, the sad fact is that there are those who take what they see a little 'too' far, not realizing that it's just a show, and that the WWE (much less 'any' wrestling promotion) isn't REAL. The idea that Baron Corbin has gotten death threats is absolutely ignorant, and those who would post such threats need to take a step back from the TV, go outside, and interact with reality.


I have been a UNDERTAKER fan since day one (1990), but I do NOT believe that a person can appear & disappear in the middle of the ring, or survive being buried alive multiple times. Taker is merely a 'character', nothing more. Baron Corbin plays a heel as part of his 'character', but at the end of the day, he is a HUMAN BEING.

I am a BARON CORBIN FAN.
